The user management UI for JIRA is much better than Crowd and can also be used standalone to manage users for other atlassian applications from JIRA itself.

Problem: To administer users from the JIRA, JIRA Administer permission is required, granting wide access to the application.  This either puts the full brunt of user management on the jira administrators, or it requires granting the service desk types administrative access to the jira instance. (neither is desirable in our case)

Request: Add a new permission level to global permissions "User Administrator" which grants access to the User and Group administration sections of the JIRA Admin UI, and possibly the ability to trigger a directory sync, but not to configure directories.

